FBIS3-27841 "dreas021_a_94012" FBIS-EAS-94-021 Document Type:Daily Report 1 February 1994 NORTHEAST ASIA Japan Firm To Open First Menswear Shop in Shanghai OW3101113094 Tokyo KYODO in English 1022 GMT 31 Jan 94 OW3101113094 Tokyo KYODO Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Tokyo, Jan. 31 KYODO -- Aoyama Trading Co., a major Japanese menswear retail chain operator, said Monday [31 January] it will open its first sales outlet in China in February in partnership with a local firm. The Hiroshima-based company said the new store, to be opened in Shanghai, will sell men's suits as well as shirts and casual wear. The company has already opened two stores in Taipei and established a subsidiary in Hong Kong. It said it also plans to expand its domestic sales network from the present 514 outlets to about 750 stores in two years.
